  "notes_normalized": "Cannabis is illegal in Kansas for recreational use under state law, but medical cannabis is available only in limited form. Cannabis remains federally illegal in United States.",
  "notes_raw": "style=\"background:#C4C9CD;\" | {{Hs|5}} Cannabis is only legal in Kansas in the form of THC free cannabidiol oil, also known as CBD. Patients would be allowed to own 12 plants or of marijuana for therapeutic purposes. Banda faced up to 30 years for her use and possession of cannabis. Supreme Court refused to hear the case. The first possession charge of less than will result in a class-B misdemeanor with up to 6 month incarceration sentence and a $1,000 fine maximum. A subsequent offense for possessing any amount can result in a fine of up to $100,000 and a sentence of up to 3½ years. Sale or distribution of any amount can result in a $300,000 to $500,000 fine and an incarceration sentence depending on the quantity and severity of the offense.",
